                            <comment id="15978275" author="davsclaus" created="Fri, 21 Apr 2017 08:13:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Its not a so good idea to use timeout (unless a high value) to give the system amble time to suspend/shutdown correctly. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15978440" author="graben" created="Fri, 21 Apr 2017 10:08:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Well, timeout is used by default (300s) and there does not a exist a &quot;forceSuspend&quot; feature. Therefor this can only be avoided by setting default timeout to infinity? Not a good idea.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16094332" author="davsclaus" created="Thu, 20 Jul 2017 08:11:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Use with timeout with a bit of care as when a timeout occur side effects can happens as the shutdown did not complete graceful.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
